						<div class="postbody">The <a href="http://www.atarihq.com/danb/files/CV-Tech.txt" class="postlink">ColecoVision memory map</a> has RAM from $6000 to $63FF, but it's mirrored all the way up to $7FFF. Its I/O map is full of mirroring as well.<br /><br />For hardware external to the CPU die, incomplete decoding is cheaper. The NES APU is completely decoded (and thus not mirrored) because it's on the same die as the CPU.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
