						<div class="postbody">If the NES was released a little bit later, maybe 1987, it could've had the following specs:<br /><br />- 8 palettes of 4 colors for BG tiles, and 8 palettes of 3 colors for sprites<br />- 16kB of CHR-ROM, 512 tiles for sprites and 512 tiles for BG<br />- 16 sprites per scanline<br />- 8x8 or 8x16 sprites (selected per sprite)<br />- CHR patterns are stored with each pair of bytes representing an 8x1 sliver<br />- 6 byte FIFO</div>

