				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">That interrupt on controller port in MD is for lightguns and RS232 communitation. When TH line is confed to be an input, and Port ints are enabled then high to low transition on the TH line creates a Port int to the 68K, in addition you can conf the VDP to freeze HV counter and read the pixel position where the Port int happened. Changing TH state by software will not cause Port ints, the change must come from external hardware (and to read normal controllers TH must be set as an output, so there can never be Port ints).</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.tmeeco.eu">http://www.tmeeco.eu</a><!-- m --></div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
							</td>
						</tr>
						</table>
					</td>
				</tr>
				</table>
			</td>
		</tr>

